14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 11-811 of Title 47, unless there
17 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. This act shall be known and may be cited as the "Talyn Bain
19 Act".
20 B. For the purposes of this section, the term "school" means a
21 public school operated by a school district or a private school, as
22 those terms are recognized under Title 70 of the Oklahoma Statutes,
23 that provides instruction in kindergarten through twelfth grade or
24 any combination of those grades.
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB2979 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 C. Upon request of the appropriate local jurisdiction, the
2 Department of Transportation shall establish a maximum forty-five-
3 mile-per-hour school zone on any portion of a state highway that
4 meets any of the following conditions:
5 1. The highway consists of four or more lanes and passes
6 directly adjacent to the property boundary of the school;
7 2. The highway has a posted speed limit of sixty-five (65)
8 miles per hour or greater, lacks a grade-separated off-ramp or
9 frontage road providing access to the school, and passes directly
10 adjacent to the property boundary of the school; or
11 3. The center line of the highway is within one hundred fifty
12 (150) yards from the school property line.
13 D. Upon completion of construction of the school zone, the
14 local jurisdiction shall be responsible for the maintenance and cost
15 of operation of all school zone signage and equipment.
16 E. The reduced speed limit established pursuant to this section
17 shall be enforceable when the beacons are flashing and during:
18 1. School drop-off and pick-up times as indicated by flashing
19 beacons on the school zone signage; and
20 2. Any additional hours designated by the school district or
21 private school and approved by the Department of Transportation.
22 The Department shall erect signage with flashing beacons to
23 clearly indicate the beginning and end of the school zone.
24
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB2979 SFLR Page 2
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 F. The Department may consult with the affected school
2 district, private school administration, municipality, or county
3 commissioners prior to establishing a school zone in an area
4 pursuant to this section.
5 G. Any violation of the speed limit established pursuant to
6 this section shall be enforced in the same manner as other school
7 zone speeding violations established pursuant to Oklahoma law.
8 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
9 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON AERONAUTICS AND TRANSPORTATION
